HTTP protocol

protocol: http or https
domain name: www.google.com
port number: :443
path: some/path/to/somewhere

http defaults to port 80
https defaults to port 443
ports are in the range 1-65535

A url gets translated into an GET request
connects to domain on port
GET <url path> HTTP/1.1 (HTTP version)
Some groups of headers
completely optional
Accept: some file types
headers are optional, and there can be as many as you want, but it is up to the server to handle them

Get response

HTTP/1.1 200 OK (http version statuscode reason phrase)
Headers
empty line
response body

400 client error
500 server error
200 status ok
418 I am a teapot

POST request

POST <url path> HTTP/1.1 (http version)
Headers
empty line
request body

POST response

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
headers
empty line
response body

For the server will use authorization as a header

Call to server
GET /event/12345 HTTP/1.1
Authorization: somestring

result
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
Content-Length: 2342

json with event data

Post call to server
POST /login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Content-Length: 34

json string

Post response
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
Content-Length: 2434

json string
